<article>
    <h1>Pita Pizza With Crispy Pork Lard, Arugula &amp; Ba&#xAD;con ($20)</h1>
    <h2></h2>
    <section>
        <a href="/singapore/the-straits-times/textview" title="The Straits Times">The Straits Times</a>
        - <a href="/singapore/the-straits-times/20200920/textview" title="The Straits Times - 2020-09-20"><time>2020-09-20</time></a>
        - <span>LIFE | FOOD &amp; DRINK</span>
        - <span role="byline"></span>
    </section>

    <p>I think crispy pork lard makes most dishes bet­ter and that is cer­tainly true in this case.</p>
    <p>Putting it on a pizza is not some­thing I would have thought of, but it works so well with the ba­con. It adds crunch and the aroma of lard is such a plea­sure.</p>
    <p>The grease is cut by the fresh arugula and cherry toma­toes, though I would like more ba­con for its smokey salti­ness.</p>
    <p>If you are not a fan of crispy lard or are watch­ing your fat in­take, just brush the bits off the pizza. I’m sure some­one at the ta­ble will be happy to fin­ish them up.</p>

